headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 34 points, 13 rebounds, nine assists and a career-high four blocks, Kristaps Porzingis scored 16 points in his return from a knee injury and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Charlotte Hornets 104-93 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has 34 points, Mavs beat Hornets in Porzingis' return

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 22 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Milwaukee Bucks easily beat the Detroit Pistons for the third time this month, 110-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo's triple-double lifts Bucks over Pistons

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 26 points as the solo superstar before soon centering a Big Three, leading the Brooklyn Nets, short-handed after agreeing to a trade for James Harden, to a 116-109 victory over the New York Knicks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Nets win while short-handed with Harden deal pending

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas had 24 points and 16 rebounds, Grayson Allen scored a season-high 20 off the bench and the Memphis Grizzlies came back to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 118-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas leads Grizzlies to 118-107 win over Timberwolves

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 26 points and the Los Angeles Lakers routed the Oklahoma City Thunder 128-99 on Wednesday night for their franchise-record seventh straight road victory to start the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James scores 26 points, Lakers roll past Thunder

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 28 points, Paul George added 27 and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans 111-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard leads Clippers past short-handed Pelicans 111-106

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored eight of his season-high 40 points in the final four minutes, and the Portland Trail Blazers tied a franchise record with 23 3-pointers to beat the Sacramento Kings 132-126 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard has 40, Blazers tie team record for 3s to beat Kings
